 different reasons.</p><p>if you’re a rabbit, the boss rabbit is the one who gets groomed by its subordinate rabbits. </p><p>but if you’re a cat… the boss cat is the one that grooms the other cats.</p><p>BOTH these idiots are going “aw yeah, it’s good to be on top &gt;:) ”</p>","content":"<p>this is actually HILARIOUS because both domestic rabbits and domestic cats practice dominance-related social grooming but for wildly different reasons.</p><p>if you&rsquo;re a rabbit, the boss rabbit is the one who gets groomed by its subordinate rabbits. </p><p>but if you&rsquo;re a cat&hellip; the boss cat is the one that grooms the other cats.</p><p>BOTH these idiots are going &ldquo;aw yeah, it&rsquo;s good to be on top &gt;:) &rdquo;</p>"}],"baseline_notes":156739,"baseline_ts":1774705101.464}